[{'name': 'Nithin M Agarwal', 'text': "My Google Review # 000361.

Who would have thought a humble namkeen shop would evolve into a chain of restaurants? Well, Haldiram‚Äôs has done just that. From their roots in the bustling Indian snack market, they have expanded their horizons to offer a full-fledged vegetarian dining experience.

You will find their small retail eat-out outlets popping up everywhere in Mumbai, from the convenience of Borivali Railway Station to the bustling malls like Infinity and Growel's 101. What sets them apart is their commitment to pure vegetarian food, devoid of any artificial additives like soda.

After indulging in a hearty vegetarian thali or a plate of chole bhature, you will be pleasantly surprised to find yourself feeling light and refreshed, rather than bloated. It is a testament to their commitment to using fresh, wholesome ingredients. This outlet has a decent seating space so that you do not feel crammed in the mall‚Äôs food court. The focus is clearly on the food, and in that department, they deliver. Weekends it is a mad rush. But that is still tolerable, then, eating the junk of burgers and pizzas and soiling your health and wealth both. Isnt it?

All types of cards and cash payments are accepted here. Parking is within the mall, so nothing to worry about it.
